Package: mxp
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, emacs | emacs-nox, bash
Description: Pipe content between terminal and Emacs buffers
 mxp is a shell script that acts as a bridge between Unix pipes and Emacs
 buffers. It supports:
 .
  * Write mode: Pipe stdin to Emacs buffers
  * Read mode: Output buffer content to stdout for piping
  * Open mode: Open files and directories in Emacs
  * Streaming: Real-time content updates with chunked processing
  * Buffer matching: Use exact names or regex patterns
  * Auto-generation: Creates *Piper 1*, *Piper 2*, etc. when no name specified
